# The built binary at the repo root. Anchored with a leading slash so it does NOT
# also match the cmd/agent-bridge-mcp/ SOURCE directory (an unanchored pattern there
# silently ignores any new .go file added to the package). The .exe variant is the
# Windows build (go env GOEXE = .exe); keep both so neither OS's binary is committed.
/agent-bridge-mcp
/agent-bridge-mcp.exe
# Temp left by `go build -o agent-bridge-mcp.exe` on Windows when the target .exe is
# locked (e.g. by a running server): go writes the new image beside it and can't rename.
/agent-bridge-mcp.exe~
*.out
.antigravitycli/
# Generated by `make install-codex`: the canonical skills live in ./skills/ and the
# built binary at the repo root; both are copied into the Codex plugin root at install
# time because Codex requires a plugin's skills/MCP binary to live inside the plugin root
# (its validator forbids `..`/symlink escapes, and the bundled .mcp.json resolves
# `./agent-bridge-mcp` relative to the installed plugin).
/plugins/agent-bridge/skills/
/plugins/agent-bridge/agent-bridge-mcp
/plugins/agent-bridge/agent-bridge-mcp.exe
# Scratch diff/patch artifacts a sub-agent (e.g. agy) writes when pointed at the repo
# as its working_dir — it saves `git diff` output to a file to inspect it. Not source.
*.patch
diff.txt
diff_*.txt
*_diff.txt
